The watermelon will always taste less sweet when it's frozen. So if it tastes even slightly sweet while frozen, it will taste super sweet when room temperature. The reason, of course, is that taste is the result of a chemical reaction occurring on your tongue and chemical reactions are slower and less intense when cold. What this translates to is that even very sweet fruits can end up rather bland if eaten frozen.
